      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "As a consequence of new snow and a strong wind from variable directions, avalanche prone wind slabs formed in the last few days. The fresh and somewhat older wind slabs are lying on the unfavourable surface of an old snowpack. <br/> <br/> Avalanche prone weak layers exist in the bottom section of the snowpack on west, north and east facing slopes. This applies above approximately 2000 m. <br/> <br/> Steep sunny slopes: Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise to increasing moistening of the snowpack."
